Dialogue: 0,00:00:00.000,00:00:11.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll give you an example. So let me say if I discretize the time derivative using forward order
Dialogue: 0,00:00:11.000,00:00:18.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I assume everybody at least know what forward order is. So it basically takes two time steps.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:18.000,00:00:25.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So k plus 1 and k are two consecutive time steps. One is at t, one is at t plus delta t.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:25.000,00:00:34.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is approximation to dEI dt at t equal to tk.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:34.000,00:00:41.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,This, let's write down the numerical solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:41.000,00:00:54.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,ek of i plus 1 plus ek of i minus 1 minus 2 ek i plus tau i.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:54.000,00:00:55.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:55.000,00:01:05.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you look at this equation, there is a condition for which the solution would not self-amplify.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:05.000,00:01:17.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,The condition is delta t has to be less than delta x squared.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:17.000,00:01:24.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Do I need over 2? No, I don't need over 2. So delta t has to be less than delta x squared.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:24.000,00:01:25.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:25.000,00:01:27.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:27.000,00:01:34.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because otherwise, because otherwise I'm going to derive a matrix equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:34.000,00:01:43.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm going to say e to the k plus 1. I'm going to define it as ek plus 1 1, ek plus 1 2, etc.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:43.000,00:01:47.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,ek plus 1 n, let's say minus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:47.000,00:01:53.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is going to be a matrix times e to the k.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:53.000,00:01:54.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,e to the k is the same vector.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:54.000,00:02:03.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,e to the k is the same vector at k plus this vector tau, which is also tau 1, etc.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:03.000,00:02:11.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,tau i, tau n minus 1, also at time step k.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:11.000,00:02:23.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if you look at the matrix, what the matrix is, OK, you probably need to rearrange the terms in this equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:23.000,00:02:26.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this is this is multiplied by delta t.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:26.000,00:02:48.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So what you need to do is you need to write down ek plus 1 is equal to eik plus delta t over delta x squared times minus 2 eik plus ei plus 1 k plus ei minus 1 k plus delta t tau ik.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:48.000,00:02:52.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the matrix is going to look like very similar.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:52.000,00:03:00.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,To the kind of matrix we derived in the last class, but a little bit different because I have this term and I have a delta t term.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:00.000,00:03:09.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the diagonals, for example, is going to be 1 minus 2 delta t over delta x squared.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:09.000,00:03:10.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:10.000,00:03:14.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,The off-diagonals is just going to be delta t over delta x squared.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:14.000,00:03:20.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is the same and the lower diagonal is also the same.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:22.000,00:03:30.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can take a look at this matrix and you can particularly look at what's called the norm of this matrix.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:30.000,00:03:36.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,OK, so let's say this matrix is A.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:36.000,00:03:40.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,The norm of the matrix.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:40.000,00:03:50.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,The norm of this matrix defines the norm of the matrix.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:50.000,00:04:03.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Defines the maximum possible ratio of A times E divided by E.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:03.000,00:04:04.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:04.000,00:04:11.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And here both the numerator and denominator are the norm of a vector.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:11.000,00:04:17.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, for example, norm of the vector E.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:17.000,00:04:18.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So E is a vector.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:18.000,00:04:19.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:20.000,00:04:27.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And here the numerator is defined as the length of the vector.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:27.000,00:04:33.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So EI 1 squared plus E2 squared plus etc plus EI minus 1 squared.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:33.000,00:04:35.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:35.000,00:04:37.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,By the way, there are many different norms.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:37.000,00:04:40.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is one of the most commonly seen norm.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:40.000,00:04:45.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's usually called the 2 norm because of the squares are power of 2.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:45.000,00:04:48.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if I'm using 2 norms for the vectors,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:48.000,00:04:51.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,the matrix norm is also called the 2 norm.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:51.000,00:04:56.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,The matrix norm is inherited from the vector norm.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:56.000,00:04:57.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:57.000,00:05:05.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,So now if the norm of the matrix is less than 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:05:05.000,00:05:13.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm fine because E is equal to A times E plus a truncation error.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:13.000,00:05:16.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,If the truncation error is small,
Dialogue: 0,00:05:16.000,00:05:21.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,then the E would be the same order of magnitude as the truncation error.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:21.000,00:05:24.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would not self-amplify.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:24.000,00:05:27.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,If the norm of the matrix is greater than 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:05:27.000,00:05:29.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,no good.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:29.000,00:05:32.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even if I have a small delta t,
