Dialogue: 0,00:10:17.640,00:10:20.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,If the analytical solution doesn't reach a steady state,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:20.640,00:10:23.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,for example, in the project when you are controlling the U
Dialogue: 0,00:10:23.640,00:10:26.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you make U sometimes bigger, sometimes smaller,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:26.640,00:10:30.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,then the analytical solution does not reach a steady state.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:30.640,00:10:33.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,And your E also would not reach a steady state.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:33.640,00:10:38.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you can bound this magnitude if you can bound the magnitude of tau.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:39.640,00:10:49.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:49.640,00:10:50.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:50.640,00:10:56.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, so the norm of A is going to be something that,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:56.640,00:11:00.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,that you can use to analyze stability of the solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:00.640,00:11:07.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this particular matrix, for example, we can,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:07.640,00:11:08.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can call this,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:08.640,00:11:12.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,dT dx2.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:12.640,00:11:18.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's call this as dT over dx square.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:18.640,00:11:24.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,If this is equal to 0.5, okay, we are going to be making a matrix A
Dialogue: 0,00:11:24.640,00:11:29.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,that is equal to 1 minus 2 times dT over dx square in the diagonal.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:29.640,00:11:36.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is 1 minus 2 times dT dx square times identity of,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:36.640,00:11:37.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,let's say, 100.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:37.640,00:11:38.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:38.640,00:11:39.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:39.640,00:11:41.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,A is that thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:41.640,00:11:46.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's actually, this is actually 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:46.640,00:11:49.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for I goes from 1 to 99,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:49.640,00:11:54.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,we are going to say A of I, I plus 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:54.640,00:11:57.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,is equal to dT dx square.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:57.640,00:12:03.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,A of I, I plus 1 and I is also equal to dT dx square.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:03.640,00:12:06.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So A is this matrix.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:06.640,00:12:07.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you type norm of A,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:07.640,00:12:11.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,you get something smaller than 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:11.640,00:12:16.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if dT dx square is equal to, let's say, 1.5,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:16.640,00:12:18.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,you are out of luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:18.640,00:12:26.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because you take A equal to this and you do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:26.640,00:12:30.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Norm of A is going to be 4.99.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:30.640,00:12:32.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you are going to get,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:32.640,00:12:35.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,so every time E is amplified by a factor of almost 5,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:35.640,00:12:36.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,you are going to get infinity.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:36.640,00:12:41.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,You are going to get infinity after a pretty finite number of time steps.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:41.640,00:12:42.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:42.640,00:12:45.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Did you say the condition for stability was A less than 1?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:45.640,00:12:46.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:46.640,00:12:48.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, norm of A is less than 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:48.640,00:12:50.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:50.640,00:12:54.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Norm of A has to be less than 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:54.640,00:12:55.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:55.640,00:12:59.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Any other questions?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:59.640,00:13:00.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:00.640,00:13:04.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So why is the norm larger than 1 still being unstable?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:04.640,00:13:06.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why is it going to be unstable?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:06.640,00:13:10.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because if the norm is greater than 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:10.640,00:13:12.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's actually a good question.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:12.640,00:13:14.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,I forgot to mention that.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:14.640,00:13:16.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,If the norm is larger than 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:16.640,00:13:20.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,that means there exists an E.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:20.640,00:13:24.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,That makes A times E to be larger than E.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:24.640,00:13:28.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:28.640,00:13:30.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,And no matter,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:30.640,00:13:33.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,so if you look at the solution,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:33.640,00:13:34.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,the truncation error tau,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:34.640,00:13:39.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,tau may have maybe a linear combination of many components.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:39.640,00:13:45.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,But only if there is one component that lies along that solution,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:45.640,00:13:51.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,that component is going to be amplified.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:51.640,00:13:53.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,And over many time steps,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:53.640,00:13:55.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,if it keeps being amplified,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:55.640,00:14:00.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,you get an unstable solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:00.640,00:14:03.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we'll discuss more about that later.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:03.640,00:14:08.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the norm of A to be less than 1 is a sufficient,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:08.640,00:14:11.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,but not necessary condition for stability.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:11.640,00:14:12.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:12.640,00:14:16.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are actually some cases where the norm of A can be larger than 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:16.640,00:14:18.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can still be stable.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:18.640,00:14:20.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,You need an eigenvalue analysis of A
Dialogue: 0,00:14:20.640,00:14:24.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,to figure out exactly if the scheme is going to be stable or not.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:24.640,00:14:29.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,You need the maximum eigenvalue to be actually less than 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:29.640,00:14:30.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in some cases,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:30.640,00:14:32.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,even if your eigenvalues are all less than 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:32.640,00:14:34.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,the norm can still be larger than 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:34.640,00:14:36.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,But usually the norm is,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:36.640,00:14:39.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,if you can make sure the norm is less than 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:39.640,00:14:42.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,you are sure you get a stable scheme.
